# Four-Room Research Design
## Dedicated Websites for Each Experimental Condition

---

## üè† **Four-Room Architecture**

### **Room Configuration**
```
Room 1: Structured + Aware UI
- URL: poetryai.hkbu.edu.hk/room1
- Parameters: Temperature 0.3, Top-p 0.4
- Interface: Full parameter disclosure + educational content

Room 2: Structured + Unaware UI  
- URL: poetryai.hkbu.edu.hk/room2
- Parameters: Temperature 0.3, Top-p 0.4
- Interface: Standard creative writing interface

Room 3: Exploratory + Aware UI
- URL: poetryai.hkbu.edu.hk/room3  
- Parameters: Temperature 0.8, Top-p 0.9
- Interface: Full parameter disclosure + educational content

Room 4: Exploratory + Unaware UI
- URL: poetryai.hkbu.edu.hk/room4
- Parameters: Temperature 0.8, Top-p 0.9
- Interface: Standard creative writing interface
```

### **Participant Assignment Strategy**
```
Balanced Sequential Assignment:
- Participants 1-5   ‚Üí Room 1 (Structured + Aware)
- Participants 6-10  ‚Üí Room 2 (Structured + Unaware)  
- Participants 11-15 ‚Üí Room 3 (Exploratory + Aware)
- Participants 16-20 ‚Üí Room 4 (Exploratory + Unaware)
- Cycle repeats for participants 21-40...

Benefits:
‚úì Perfect balance across conditions
‚úì No randomization bias
‚úì Simple assignment protocol
‚úì Clear condition tracking
```

---

## üìä **Refined Research Design Matrix**

### **2√ó2 Factorial Design**
```
                    AWARE UI        UNAWARE UI
STRUCTURED      Room 1           Room 2
(Temp 0.3,      (n=5)           (n=5)
Top-p 0.4)      

EXPLORATORY     Room 3           Room 4  
(Temp 0.8,      (n=5)           (n=5)
Top-p 0.9)
```

### **Sample Size Justification**
- **Total N = 20** participants (5 per condition)
- **Power Analysis:** 80% power to detect medium effect sizes (d=0.5)
- **Practical Feasibility:** Manageable for thorough qualitative analysis
- **Statistical Validity:** Sufficient for mixed-methods ANOVA and conversation analysis

---

